CVE-2026-41520
# kubescape: docker CVE is a Moby authorization plugin bypass, not applicable as kubescape is a static scanner that does not interact with Docker auth plugins
CVE-2026-34040
# kubescape + grype + syft + trivy: go-git CVE-2026-45022 is improper parsing of malformed git commit/tag objects affecting commit signature verification. Affected tools at their latest releases (kubescape v4.0.8, grype v0.112.0, syft v1.44.0, trivy v0.70.0) still pin go-git v5.17.x/v5.18.0. Not applicable as all four are used as static scanners on local files and do not parse attacker-controlled git objects or perform commit signature verification. Remove when upstream tools upgrade to go-git >=5.19.0.
CVE-2026-45022

# protolint + terrascan: both embed grpc-go; CVE-2026-33186 requires a running gRPC server with grpc/authz interceptors - both tools run as CLI static linters and never start an authorized gRPC server; remove when upgraded to grpc-go >=1.79.3
CVE-2026-33186

# shfmt: Go stdlib CVEs in v3.13.1 (latest release, compiled with Go 1.26.1). shfmt is a pure shell script formatter that reads files and writes formatted output - it makes no DNS lookups, HTTP/2 connections, network dials, or email address parsing. Remove when shfmt releases a build with Go >=1.26.3.
